          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Tax Cuts and Jobs Middle Class Enhancement Act </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude from gross income up to $5,000 received by an individual as a bonus after December 22, 2017, and before January 1, 2019. The bill defines a "bonus" as amounts paid to an employee other than amounts obligated under an employment contract. </p> <p>The bill makes permanent the tax reductions and other provisions for individuals that were enacted in P.L 115-97 (commonly known as the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act) and are scheduled to expire at the end of 2025.</p> <p>The bill also: </p> <ul> <li>increases the standard deduction, </li> <li> makes permanent the reduction in the adjusted gross income threshold that must be exceeded before a taxpayer is allowed to claim an itemized deduction for medical expenses, and</li> <li> increases the refundable portion of the child tax credit. </li> </ul>]]></text>
